!! !!Morphophonology
! ---------------
!! To represent phonologic variations in word forms we use the following
!! symbols in the lexicon files:

 %{aäPar%} !!= * @CODE@  no diphthongs
 %{aäDiph%} !!= * @CODE@  This is for diphthongs such as the infinitive marker after i and u stems
 %{oö%}  !!= * @CODE@
 %{oöØ%} !!= * @CODE@  Used in present participle
 %{uy%}  !!= * @CODE@
 %{ui%} !!= @CODE@ in imperative before %{aä%}:
 A2      !!= * @CODE@  used with verb types V_AVATA
 %{ijPRC%} !!= * @CODE@ participle

